四分之一世紀是一段漫長的時間
A quarter century is a long time.

1613
01:41:20,040 --> 01:41:21,980
到巴格比的店時
By the time we reached Bagby's store,

1614
01:41:21,980 --> 01:41:23,610
我的手已經黑了
my hand had turned black.

1615
01:41:24,470 --> 01:41:26,660
截肢的時候我還處於昏迷中
I was not awake when I lost the arm.

1616
01:41:30,040 --> 01:41:32,490
他們說考伯恩警官一直陪著我
The Marshal had stayed with me, I was told.

1617
01:41:32,490 --> 01:41:33,850
直到我脫離險境
'til I was out of danger.

1618
01:41:34,230 --> 01:41:36,280
但他在我醒來之前就離開了
But he departed before I came around.

1619
01:41:37,190 --> 01:41:39,860
一到家  我就給他發了邀請
Once home. I wrote him with an invitation,

1620
01:41:39,860 --> 01:41:42,840
請他下次經過耶爾縣的時候過來坐坐
to come by, the next time he found himself near Yell County.

1621
01:41:43,270 --> 01:41:45,930
並收下我欠他的五十塊錢
And collect the fifty dollars I still owed him.

1622
01:41:46,830 --> 01:41:48,780
我沒有收到考伯恩警官的回音
I did not hear back from Marshal Cogburn.

1623
01:41:49,100 --> 01:41:50,490
他也沒再出現
And he did not appear.

1624
01:41:52,820 --> 01:41:54,270
有一天我收到了警官的字條
Then one day I received a note from the Marshal,

1625
01:41:54,270 --> 01:41:56,890
還附了張傳單
with a flyer enclosed.

1626
01:41:54,510 --> 01:41:59,200
科爾·揚戈與弗蘭克·詹姆斯
狂野西部特別獻映  每天兩場

